<br>
I mean, a character has some total number of exp he's earned - if the amount of exp required to lvl is lowered for 30, 35, 40, and 45, and he's, say 46, then the TOTAL needed for 46 is now lower - and he's got more than that since he's been through hells, so what happens?<br>
<br>
Verant can't just average out the hell level exp across all lvls, making each level a bit harder - in that case, someone, say lvl 29, suddenedly doens't have enough exp for 29, since the hell exp needed for 35, 40, 45, etc., has been averaged across all lvl's...can you imagine the howl if players LOST lvls because of this?<br>
<br>
Maybe Verant is just gonna adjust the amount of exp that every character has earned to accomodate the new exp model, i.e., your lvl doesn't change, but the total exp you've earned does to match whereever you are in your current lvl...still, that's not really fair, since the amount of TIME it took to get through 30, 35, 40, and 45 is still lost, i.e., with lower exp requirements, I should have made it through faster...<br>
